    "Name": "Broadside",
    "Details": "The Broadside is a relatively new chassis to the battlefields of the Inner Sphere but Solaris VII never misses an opportunity for innovation. In that vein comes Blunderbuss, a Broadside with a knock-out punch. Built on the same Endo-Steel skeleton as the regular Broadside, the Blunderbuss swaps the rugged standard engine for an advanced Clan-grade 300-rated XL. It uses this extra free weight to mount a dizzying array of firepower, with a Silver Bullet Gauss Rifle and a Hyper-Assault Gauss Rifle/30 forming the core of the array. An Clan-spec Gauss Rifle and ER PPC round out the guns, ensuring that the Blunderbuss can one-tap just about anything it can catch. The heat is decently managed by the 12 double heat sinks mounted to it.<br><br>X-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
